cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the adoption and user acceptance of a blockchain-based research data sharing system, which involves data management, security, and usability aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which covers topics related to the social and ethical aspects of computing technologies. The paper also discusses the security and privacy aspects of the system, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper discusses the usability and user experience of the system, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
